gov.usgs.anss.edgemom

Class GapsFromInorderChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edgemom.GapsFromInorderChannel

  • public class GapsFromInorderChannel
extends java.lang.Object
    this class is used by GapFromInorderMaker to process the data and create gap entries. It is called statically via method process() which will create one object of this type for every new channel. This class process() method checks for gaps and overlaps and keeps statistics on same.

      • process

        public boolean process(java.lang.StringBuilder seed,
                       long time,
                       int nsamp,
                       double rate)
        process a trace buf, if it overlaps or is prior return true to indicate skip is needed if data is to remain strictly in increasing order.
        Parameters:
        seed - The SB with a 12 character NSCL
        time - The time in millis
        nsamp - The number of samples in this packet
        rate - The data rate in Hz
        Returns:
        if true, this packet should be skipped to keep things strictly in increasing order
